# Dataset — large binary/data, machine-specific symlinks, not tracked
# in git. Both `dataset/` (directory) and `dataset` (symlink/file) must
# be ignored — historically `dataset` was committed as a symlink to
# `/inspire/.../dataset` which only resolved on the cloud env and
# broke every other machine on git pull/reset.
dataset
dataset/
dataset.zip
news_merged.zip

# Large slide deck — exceeds GitHub 100MB single-file limit
*.pptx

# Prebuilt indexes — rebuilt from dataset, not tracked
# reference_submission/index/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
dist/
build/

# Env — .env IS tracked (private repo; cloud eval pulls config from git)

# Local-only smoke-test deps (eval box installs from requirements.txt)
.deps/

# Provided resources — injected by the cloud/eval env, not our code
# (problem set incl. ground truth, and baseline reference prompts)
# reference_submission/problem/
# reference_submission/prompt_templates/reference_generate.md
# reference_submission/prompt_templates/reference_review.md

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/

generatedataset/
docs/